Champion																					CATEGORY:CLASS
Initial Proficiencies			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Initial Proficiencies					SOURCEPAGE:p.106	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01					DESC:At 1st level, you gain a number of proficiencies that represent your basic training, noted at the start of this class.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								ABILITY:PROFICIENCY|AUTOMATIC|Perception|Fortitude|Fortitude|Will|Will|Reflex|Religion|Simple Weapons|Martial Weapons|Unarmed Attacks|Light Armor|Medium Armor|Heavy Armor|Shields|Champion Class DC|Divine Spell Attacks|Divine Spell DCs																																					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Class Ability Boost Strength or Dexterity|1	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Trained Skills|2+INT	BONUS:VAR|GainDeityLoreSkill|1|TYPE=Boolean
Champion's Code				KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Champion's Code						SOURCEPAGE:p.106	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01					DESC:You follow a code of conduct, beginning with tenets shared by all champions of an alignment (such as good), and continuing with tenets of your cause. Deities often add additional strictures (for instance, Torag's champions can't show mercy to enemies of their people, making it almost impossible for them to follow the redeemer cause). Only rules for good champions appear in this book. Tenets are listed in order of importance, starting with the most important. If a situation places two tenets in conflict, you aren't in a no-win situation; instead, follow the more important tenet. For instance, as a paladin, if an evil king asked you if you're hiding refugees so he could execute them, you could lie to him, since the tenet against lying is less important than preventing harm to innocents. Trying to subvert your code by creating a situation that forces a higher tenet to override a lower tenet (for example, promising not to respect authorities and then, to keep your word, disrespecting authorities) is a violation of the champion code. If you stray from your alignment or violate your code of conduct, you lose your focus pool and divine ally until you demonstrate your repentance by conducting an atone ritual (page 409), but you keep any other champion abilities that don't require those class features. If your alignment shifts but is still one allowed by your deity, your GM might let you retrain your cause while still following the same deity. &nl;The Tenets of Good &nl;All champions of good alignment follow these tenets. &nl;You must never perform acts anathema to your deity or willingly commit an evil act, such as murder, torture, or the casting of an evil spell. &nl;You must never knowingly harm an innocent, or allow immediate harm to one through inaction when you know you could reasonably prevent it. This tenet doesn't force you to take action against possible harm to innocents at an indefinite time in the future, or to sacrifice your life to protect them.
Deity and Cause				KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Deity and Cause						SOURCEPAGE:p.106	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01					DESC:Champions are divine servants of a deity. Choose a deity to follow (pages 437-440); your alignment must be one allowed for followers of your deity. Actions fundamentally opposed to your deity's ideals or alignment are anathema to your faith. A few examples of acts that would be considered anathema appear in each deity's entry. You and your GM determine whether other acts are anathema. You have one of the following causes. Your cause must match your alignment exactly. Your cause determines your champion's reaction, grants you a devotion spell (page 107), and defines part of your champion's code.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Champion Deity and Cause|1
Deific Weapon				KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Deific Weapon						SOURCEPAGE:p.107	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01					DESC:You zealously bear your deity's favored weapon. If it's uncommon, you gain access to it. If it's a simple weapon, increase the damage die by one step (d4 to d6, d6 to d8, d8 to d10, d10 to d12).
Champion's Reaction			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Champion's Reaction					SOURCEPAGE:p.107	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01					DESC:Your cause gives you a special reaction: Retributive Strike for paladin, Glimpse of Redemption for redeemer, or Liberating Step for liberator.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				ABILITY:Champion Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Champion Class Feature ~ Champion's Reaction / RETRIBUTIVE STRIKE|PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Champion_Paladin=true	ABILITY:Champion Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Champion Class Feature ~ Champion's Reaction / GLIMPSE OF REDEMPTION|PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Champion_Redeemer=true	ABILITY:Champion Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Champion Class Feature ~ Champion's Reaction / LIBERATING STEP|PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Champion_Liberator=true
Devotion Spells				KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Devotion Spells						SOURCEPAGE:p.108	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01					DESC:Your deity's power grants you special divine spells called devotion spells, which are a type of focus spell. It costs 1 Focus Point to cast a focus spell, and you start with a focus pool of 1 Focus Point. You refill your focus pool during your daily preparations, and you regain 1 Focus Point by spending 10 minutes using the Refocus activity to pray to your deity or do service toward their causes. Focus spells are automatically heightened to half your level rounded up. Certain feats can give you more focus spells and increase the size of your focus pool, though your focus pool can never hold more than 3 Focus Points. The full rules are on page 300. You gain a devotion spell depending on your cause, and you are trained in divine spell attack rolls and spell DCs. Your spellcasting ability is Charisma.																																																																																																																																																																																																					ABILITY:Proficiency|AUTOMATIC|Divine Spell Attack Rolls|Divine Spell DC	ABILITY:Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|focus pool																																																																											BONUS:VAR|FocusPool|1
Champion Feats				KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Champion Feats						SOURCEPAGE:p.108	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01					DESC:At 1st level and every even-numbered level thereafter, you gain a champion class feat. Champion class feats are presented beginning on page 109.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Class Feats|1+floor(TL/2)
Shield Block				KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Shield Block							SOURCEPAGE:p.108	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01					DESC:You gain the Shield Block general feat (page 266), a reaction that lets you reduce damage with your shield.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										ABILITY:FEAT|AUTOMATIC|Shield Block
Divine Ally 3rd				KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Divine Ally							SOURCEPAGE:p.108	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 03					DESC:Your devotion attracts a spirit of your deity's alignment. Once you choose an ally, your choice can't be changed. The following are divine allies:	DESC:&nl;Blade Ally: A spirit of battle dwells within your weapon. Select one weapon when you make your daily preparations. In your hands, the weapon gains the effect of a property rune. For a champion following the tenets of good, choose disrupting, ghost touch, returning, or shifting. You also gain the weapon's critical specialization effect.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Class Feature,Champion Class Feature ~ Divine Ally / Blade Ally	DESC:&nl;Shield Ally: A spirit of protection dwells within your shield. In your hands, the shield's Hardness increases by 2 and its HP and BT increase by half.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Class Feature,Champion Class Feature ~ Divine Ally / Shield Ally	DESC:&nl;Steed Ally: You gain a young animal companion as a mount (page 214). Ordinarily, your animal companion is one that has the mount special ability, such as a horse. You can select a different animal companion (GM's discretion), but this ability doesn't grant it the mount special ability.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Class Feature,Champion Class Feature ~ Divine Ally / Steed Ally																																																																																																																																																																																																												BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Champion Divine Ally|1
Weapon Expertise 5th			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Weapon Expertise						SOURCEPAGE:p.108	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 05					DESC:You've dedicated yourself to learning the intricacies of your weapons. Your proficiency ranks for simple weapons and martial weapons increase to expert.
Armor Expertise 7th			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Armor Expertise						SOURCEPAGE:p.108	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 07					DESC:You have spent so much time in armor that you know how to make the most of its protection. Your proficiency ranks for light, medium, and heavy armor, as well as for unarmored defense, increase to expert. You gain the armor specialization effects of medium and heavy armor.
Weapon Specialization 7th		KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Weapon Specialization					SOURCEPAGE:p.108	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 07					DESC:You've learned how to inflict greater injuries with the weapons you know best. You deal 2 additional damage with weapons and unarmed attacks in which you are an expert. This damage increases to 3 if you're a master, and to 4 if you're legendary.
Champion Expertise 9th			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Champion Expertise						SOURCEPAGE:p.108	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 09					DESC:Prayers strengthen your divine power. Your proficiency ranks for your champion class DC and divine spell attack rolls and DCs increase to expert.
Divine Smite 9th				KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Divine Smite							SOURCEPAGE:p.108	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 09					DESC:Your champion's reaction improves.	DESC:&nl;Paladin: You surround evil targets in a punishing halo. If you hit with your Retributive Strike, the target takes persistent good damage equal to your Charisma modifier.|PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Champion_Paladin=true	DESC:&nl;Redeemer: A guilty conscience assails foes who spurn your Glimpse of Redemption. A foe that responds to your Glimpse of Redemption by dealing damage takes persistent good damage equal to your Charisma modifier.|PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Champion_Redeemer=true	DESC:&nl;Liberator: You punish those who ensnare your allies in bondage. If the triggering enemy was using any effects to make your ally grabbed, restrained, immobilized, or paralyzed when you used Liberating Step, that enemy takes persistent good damage equal to your Charisma modifier.|PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Champion_Liberator=true
Juggernaut 9th				KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Juggernaut							SOURCEPAGE:p.109	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 09					DESC:Your body is accustomed to physical hardship and resistant to ailments. Your proficiency rank for Fortitude saves increases to master. When you roll a success on a Fortitude save, you get a critical success instead.
Lightning Reflexes 9th			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Lightning Reflexes						SOURCEPAGE:p.109	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 09					DESC:Your reflexes are lightning fast. Your proficiency rank for Reflex saves increases to expert.
Alertness 11th				KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Alertness							SOURCEPAGE:p.109	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 11					DESC:You remain alert to threats around you. Your proficiency rank for Perception increases to expert.
Divine Will 11th				KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Divine Will							SOURCEPAGE:p.109	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 11					DESC:Your faith grants mastery of your will. Your proficiency rank for Will saves increases to master. When you roll a success on a Will save, you get a critical success instead.
Exalt 11th					KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Exalt								SOURCEPAGE:p.109	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 11					DESC:Your champion's reaction exalts nearby allies, allowing them to benefit as well.	DESC:&nl;Paladin: When you use Retributive Strike, each ally within 15 feet of you with the target in their melee reach can spend a reaction to Strike the target with a -5 penalty.|PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Champion_Paladin=true	DESC:&nl;Redeemer: You protect multiple allies. You can apply the resistance granted by Glimpse of Redemption to yourself and all allies within 15 feet of you, including the triggering ally, except the resistance is reduced by 2 for all.|PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Champion_Redeemer=true	DESC:&nl;Liberator: You can help your whole group get into position. When you use Liberating Step, if your ally doesn't attempt to break free of an effect, you and all allies within 15 feet can Step, in addition to the triggering ally.|PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Champion_Liberator=true
Armor Mastery 13th			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Armor Mastery						SOURCEPAGE:p.109	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 13					DESC:Your skill with armor improves, helping you avoid more blows. Your proficiency ranks for light, medium, and heavy armor, as well as for unarmored defense, increase to master.
Weapon Mastery 13th			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Weapon Mastery						SOURCEPAGE:p.109	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 13					DESC:You fully understand your weapons. Your proficiency ranks for simple and martial weapons increase to master.
Greater Weapon Specialization 15th	KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Greater Weapon Specialization				SOURCEPAGE:p.109	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 15					DESC:Your damage from weapon specialization increases to 4 with weapons and unarmed attacks in which you're an expert, 6 if you're a master, and 8 if you're legendary.
Champion Mastery 17th			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Champion Mastery						SOURCEPAGE:p.109	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 17					DESC:You've mastered your arsenal of champion techniques and divine spells. Your proficiency ranks for your champion class DC and for divine spell attack rolls and spell DCs increase to master.
Legendary Armor 17th			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Legendary Armor						SOURCEPAGE:p.109	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 17					DESC:You shield yourself with steel as easily as with faith. Your proficiency ranks for light, medium, and heavy armor, as well as for unarmored defense, increase to legendary.
Hero's Defiance 19th			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Hero's Defiance						SOURCEPAGE:p.109	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 19					DESC:You can defy fate and continue fighting as long as you have divine energy. You gain the hero's defiance devotion spell.

# Deity and Cause
Paladin (Lawful Good)			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Deity and Cause / Paladin				SOURCEPAGE:p.106	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01.Champion Deity and Cause	DESC:You're honorable, forthright, and committed to pushing back the forces of cruelty. You gain the Retributive Strike champion's reaction and the lay on hands devotion spell. After the tenets of good, add these tenets: &nl;You must act with honor, never taking advantage of others, lying, or cheating. &nl;You must respect the lawful authority of legitimate leadership wherever you go, and follow its laws.
Redeemer (Neutral Good)			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Deity and Cause / Redeemer				SOURCEPAGE:p.106	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01.Champion Deity and Cause	DESC:You're full of kindness and forgiveness. You gain the Glimpse of Redemption champion's reaction and the lay on hands devotion spell. After the tenets of good, add these: &nl;You must first try to redeem those who commit evil acts, rather than killing them or meting out punishment. If they then continue on a wicked path, you might need to take more extreme measures. &nl;You must show compassion for others, regardless of their authority or station.
Liberator (Chaotic Good)		KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Deity and Cause / Liberator				SOURCEPAGE:p.107	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01.Champion Deity and Cause	DESC:You're committed to defending the freedom of others. You gain the Liberating Step champion's reaction and the lay on hands devotion spell. After the tenets of good, add these tenets: &nl;You must respect the choices others make over their own lives, and you can't force someone to act in a particular way or threaten them if they don't. &nl;You must demand and fight for others' freedom to make their own decisions. You may never engage in or countenance slavery or tyranny.

# Champion's Reaction
Retributive Strike			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Champion's Reaction / Retributive Strike		SOURCEPAGE:p.107	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01.reaction			DESC:Trigger An enemy damages your ally, and both are within 15 feet of you. &nl;You protect your ally and strike your foe. The ally gains resistance to all damage against the triggering damage equal to 2 + your level. If the foe is within reach, make a melee Strike against it.
Glimpse Of Redemption			KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Champion's Reaction / Glimpse Of Redemption	SOURCEPAGE:p.107	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01.reaction			DESC:Trigger An enemy damages your ally, and both are within 15 feet of you. &nl;Your foe hesitates under the weight of sin as visions of redemption play in their mind's eye. The foe must choose one of the following options: &nl;The ally is unharmed by the triggering damage. &nl;The ally gains resistance to all damage against the triggering damage equal to 2 + your level. After the damaging effect is applied, the enemy becomes enfeebled 2 until the end of its next turn.
Liberating Step				KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Champion's Reaction / Liberating Step		SOURCEPAGE:p.107	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 01.reaction			DESC:Trigger An enemy damages, Grabs, or Grapples your ally, and both are within 15 feet of you. &nl;You free an ally from restraint. If the trigger was an ally taking damage, the ally gains resistance to all damage against the triggering damage equal to 2 + your level. The ally can attempt to break free of effects grabbing, restraining, immobilizing, or paralyzing them. They either attempt a new save against one such effect that allows a save, or attempt to Escape from one effect as a free action. If they can move, the ally can Step as a free action, even if they didn't need to escape.

# Champion Divine Ally
Blade Ally					KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Divine Ally / Blade Ally					SOURCEPAGE:p.108	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 03.Champion Divine Ally	DESC:A spirit of battle dwells within your weapon. Select one weapon when you make your daily preparations. In your hands, the weapon gains the effect of a property rune. For a champion following the tenets of good, choose disrupting, ghost touch, returning, or shifting. You also gain the weapon's critical specialization effect.
Shield Ally					KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Divine Ally / Shield Ally				SOURCEPAGE:p.108	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 03.Champion Divine Ally	DESC:A spirit of protection dwells within your shield. In your hands, the shield's Hardness increases by 2 and its HP and BT increase by half.
Steed Ally					KEY:Champion Class Feature ~ Divine Ally / Steed Ally					SOURCEPAGE:p.108	CATEGORY:Class Feature	TYPE:Champion Class Feature.Class Feature.Display.Level 03.Champion Divine Ally	DESC:You gain a young animal companion as a mount (page 214). Ordinarily, your animal companion is one that has the mount special ability, such as a horse. You can select a different animal companion (GM's discretion), but this ability doesn't grant it the mount special ability.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				FOLLOWERS:Animal Companion|1	COMPANIONLIST:Animal Companion|RACESUBTYPE=AC
